"tlg0059_tlg020.S210605" [label=<<b>SUPPORT</b><br/>           Socrates           <br/>217e<br/><i>form: general-to-particular</i><br/><font point-size="12">"τοῦτο τοίνυν ἐρωτῶ ... οὔ; ... ἄρα"</font>>, gephi_label="SUPP", text="τοῦτο τοίνυν ἐρωτῶ νῦν δή, εἰ ᾧ ἄν τι παρῇ, τοιοῦτον ἔσται τὸ ἔχον οἷον τὸ παρόν · ἢ ἐὰν μὲν κατά τινα τρόπον παρῇ, ἔσται, ἐὰν δὲ μή, οὔ; ... ἄρα", locus="217e", speaker="Socrates", form="general-to-particular", paraphrasis="\"( When something is present, not[ that which possesses (what is present to it) is such as what is present ] )\" + \"( When something is present, if this is present in a certain way, that which possesses (what is present to it) is such as what is present )\" + \"( When something is present, if this is present not in a certain way, not[ that which possesses (what is present to it) is such as what is present ] )\" JUSTIFIES/explains) \"There are times in which, when bad is present, what is neither bad nor good is not yet bad, and others in which this has already become bad\" ", manifestation="explicit", fillcolor="#dae8fc", color="#7c9ac7", style="filled", shape="ellipse", margin="0.05,0.02", source="tlg0059_tlg020"];

