"tlg0656_tlg001.T202317" -> "tlg0656_tlg001.S203846_employed" [dir=none, color="#d79c02", style="solid"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.T211310" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>     Dioscorides-Pedanius     <br/>5.82 (of <i>div</i>)<br/><i>The best lead dross is that which looks like lead<br/>white, is dense and difficult to break, contains<br/>nothing leaden, is quince-like in colour, and<br/>glassy<br/></i><font point-size="12">"σκωρία δὲ μολύβδου ... καὶ ὑαλίζουσα"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="5.82_div", speaker="Dioscorides-Pedanius", text="σκωρία δὲ μολύβδου ἐστὶν ἀρίστη ἡ ψιμυθιοφανής, πυκνὴ δὲ καὶ δύσθραυστος, μηδὲν ἔχουσα μολυβδῶδες, μηλινοειδὴς δὲ τῷ χρώματι καὶ ὑαλίζουσα", paraphrasis="The best lead dross is that which looks like lead white, is dense and difficult to break, contains nothing leaden, is quince-like in colour, and glassy ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0656_tlg001", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.T213927" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>     Dioscorides-Pedanius     <br/>5.88.1 (of <i>div</i>)<br/><i>In order for (white and effective) lead white to<br/>come about in the best variety - to be used for<br/>ophthalmological properties - as well as in worse<br/>varieties, .(In summer, ) pour most pungent<br/>vinegar into a broad-mouthed jar OR pot-bellied<br/>clay jar, .Place a leaden brick on a lattice of<br/>reeds, .Lay the lattice of reeds with the leaden<br/>brick onto the mouth of the pot, .Above, throw<br/>over covers to prevent vinegar from evaporating,<br/>.Wait until (the leaden brick), crumbling down,<br/>has strained through (the lattice), .Decant away<br/>the clean fluid that floats on top (of the vinegar<br/>after the leaden brick has crumbled down in it),<br/>.Pour the (remaining) viscous fluid into a vessel,<br/>.Let the viscous fluid dry under the sun, .Smooth<br/>the dried substance with a hand-mill OR in any<br/>way, .Sift the ground substance, .The substance<br/>that is sifted away is the better variety of<br/>(white and effective) lead white, that should be<br/>picked also for ophthalmological properties, .Thin<br/>(with a hand-mill OR in any way) and sift what<br/>remains (above the sieve) of the solid substance<br/>{, repeat, and do it again a third and fourth<br/>time}, .The substances that are sifted away at<br/>each repeated thinning and sifting are<br/>progressively worse varieties of (white and<br/>effective) lead white<br/></i><font point-size="12">"ψιμύθιον δὲ γίνεται ... τέταρτον ποιητέον"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="5.88.1_div", speaker="Dioscorides-Pedanius", text="ψιμύθιον δὲ γίνεται οὕτως · εἰς πιθάκνην πλατύστομον ἢ κεραμεᾶν γάστραν ἐγχέας δριμύτατον ὄξος ἀπέρεισαι μολυβδίνην πλίνθον ἐπὶ τὸ στόμα τοῦ κεραμίου, προυποκειμένου καλαμίνου ῥίπου, ἄνωθέν τε αὐτῆς ἐπίρριψον σκεπάσματα πρὸς τὸ μὴ διαπνεῖσθαι τὸ ὀξος · ὡς δʼ ἂν καταρρυεῖσα διαπέσῃ, τὸ μὲν ἐπαιωρούμενον καὶ καθαρὸν ὑγρὸν ἀπηθητέον, τὸ δὲ γλοιῶδες εἰς ἀγγεῖον ἐγχυτέον καὶ ξηραντέον ἐν ἡλίῳ. εἶτα ἀλεστέον ἐν χειρομυλίῳ ἢ λεαντέον ἄλλως καὶ σηστέον, 2 καὶ μετὰ ταῦτα τὸ λοιπὸν τοῦ στερεμνίου λεπτοποιητέον καὶ σηστέον, ἐναλλάξ τε τὰ αὐτὰ καὶ τρίτον καὶ τέταρτον ποιητέον", paraphrasis="In order for (white and effective) lead white to come about in the best variety - to be used for ophthalmological properties - as well as in worse varieties, .(In summer, ) pour most pungent vinegar into a broad-mouthed jar OR pot-bellied clay jar, .Place a leaden brick on a lattice of reeds, .Lay the lattice of reeds with the leaden brick onto the mouth of the pot, .Above, throw over covers to prevent vinegar from evaporating, .Wait until (the leaden brick), crumbling down, has strained through (the lattice), .Decant away the clean fluid that floats on top (of the vinegar after the leaden brick has crumbled down in it), .Pour the (remaining) viscous fluid into a vessel, .Let the viscous fluid dry under the sun, .Smooth the dried substance with a hand-mill OR in any way, .Sift the ground substance, .The substance that is sifted away is the better variety of (white and effective) lead white, that should be picked also for ophthalmological properties, .Thin (with a hand-mill OR in any way) and sift what remains (above the sieve) of the solid substance {, repeat, and do it again a third and fourth time}, .The substances that are sifted away at each repeated thinning and sifting are progressively worse varieties of (white and effective) lead white ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0656_tlg001", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

