"tlg0656_tlg001.T175521" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>     Dioscorides-Pedanius     <br/>5.88.1 (of <i>div</i>)<br/><i>The better variety, first to be sifted away, of<br/>(white and effective) lead white should be picked<br/>also for ophthalmological properties<br/></i><font point-size="12">"ψιμύθιον ... ἄμεινον ... τὸ ... παραλημπτέον δυνάμεις"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="5.88.1_div", speaker="Dioscorides-Pedanius", text="ψιμύθιον ... ἄμεινον ... τὸ πρῶτον ἀποσησθέν, ὃ καὶ εἰς τὰς ὀφθαλμικὰς παραλημπτέον δυνάμεις", paraphrasis="The better variety, first to be sifted away, of (white and effective) lead white should be picked also for ophthalmological properties ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0656_tlg001", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];
}

"tlg0656_tlg001.T165902" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>     Dioscorides-Pedanius     <br/>5.88.3 (of <i>div</i>)<br/><i>(In order for (white and effective) lead white to<br/>come about (in the best variety - to be used for<br/>ophthalmological properties - as well as in worse<br/>varieties),) Some (. (In summer, ) pour most<br/>pungent vinegar into a vessel {as per phase 1 of<br/>the 1st recipe for lead white} ), (. They place a<br/>leaden brick on a lattice (of reeds) {as per phase<br/>2 of the 1st recipe for lead white} ), .They lay a<br/>piece of wood in the middle of the vessel, .They<br/>place the lattice (with the leaden brick) on top<br/>of the piece of wood in such a way that the former<br/>does not touch the vinegar, .They close the mouth<br/>of the vessel (with a lid), .They smear it all<br/>around (in such a way as to seal it), .They leave<br/>the thus closed vessel alone (under the sun) {for<br/>10 days}, .Removing the lid, they look into the<br/>vessel, .{When the (leaden brick) has dissolved},<br/>they do the same as in {phases 6 to 13 of the 1st<br/>recipe for lead white}<br/></i><font point-size="12">"τινὲς δὲ κατὰ ... τοῖς προειρημένοις"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="5.88.3_div", speaker="Dioscorides-Pedanius", text="τινὲς δὲ κατὰ μέσον τὸ ἀγγεῖον κατερείσαντες 3 ξύλον, τὸν ῥῖπον ἐπιτιθέασιν ὡς μὴ ψαύειν τοῦ ὄξους, τὸ δὲ στόμα αὐτοῦ πωμάσαντες καὶ περιχρίσαντες ἐῶσι καὶ ... δι ὰ ι ´ ἡμερῶν ἀφαιρούμενοι τὸ πῶμα ἐπισκοποῦνται · ὅταν δὲ διαλυθῇ, τὰ ἄλλα ποιοῦσιν ὁμοίως τοῖς προειρημένοις", paraphrasis="(In order for (white and effective) lead white to come about (in the best variety - to be used for ophthalmological properties - as well as in worse varieties),) Some (. (In summer, ) pour most pungent vinegar into a vessel {as per phase 1 of the 1st recipe for lead white} ), (. They place a leaden brick on a lattice (of reeds) {as per phase 2 of the 1st recipe for lead white} ), .They lay a piece of wood in the middle of the vessel, .They place the lattice (with the leaden brick) on top of the piece of wood in such a way that the former does not touch the vinegar, .They close the mouth of the vessel (with a lid), .They smear it all around (in such a way as to seal it), .They leave the thus closed vessel alone (under the sun) {for 10 days}, .Removing the lid, they look into the vessel, .{When the (leaden brick) has dissolved}, they do the same as in {phases 6 to 13 of the 1st recipe for lead white} ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0656_tlg001", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.T165902_referenced-in_tlg0656_tlg001.T214145_1" [label=<IS REFERENCED IN>, fontsize="11", style="rounded,filled", fillcolor="#f0f3e0", color="#708238", shape="note"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.T185635" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>     Dioscorides-Pedanius     <br/>5.88.3 (of <i>div</i>)<br/><i>To shape ((white and effective) lead white) (into<br/>lozenges), .(In summer,) knead (the lead white)<br/>with pungent vinegar, .Make it into shapes, .Leave<br/>it to dry under the sun<br/></i><font point-size="12">"εἰ δὲ ἀναπλάσαι ... ἐν ἡλίῳ"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="5.88.3_div", speaker="Dioscorides-Pedanius", text="εἰ δὲ ἀναπλάσαι θέλοι τις αὐτό, ὄξει δριμεῖ φυρατέον καὶ οὕτως ἀναπλαστέον καὶ ξηραντέον ἐν ἡλίῳ", paraphrasis="To shape ((white and effective) lead white) (into lozenges), .(In summer,) knead (the lead white) with pungent vinegar, .Make it into shapes, .Leave it to dry under the sun ", manifestation="explicit", source="tlg0656_tlg001", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"tlg0656_tlg001.T185635_referenced-in_tlg0656_tlg001.T214145_1" [label=<IS REFERENCED IN>, fontsize="11", style="rounded,filled", fillcolor="#f0f3e0", color="#708238", shape="note"];

