"caley_richards_1956.T211944" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.<br/>p. 188<br/><i>It has generally been overlooked in scholarly<br/>literature about basic lead carbonate production<br/>methods in antiquity that \"In the small-scale<br/>processes used by the ancients to produce basic<br/>lead carbonate, air and the water used in the<br/>washing operations provided enough carbon dioxide<br/>to obtain this product\"<br/></i><font point-size="12">"What has been ... an- cients"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="p. 188", speaker="Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.", text="What has been ···- ······ ·········· ·· ···· the air itself ··· ··· ····· ···· ·· ··· ······· ·········· ········ ······ ······ ······· ·· ······· ····· ···· ········· ·· ··· ·····- ····· ········· ···· ·· ··· an- cients", paraphrasis="It has generally been overlooked in scholarly literature about basic lead carbonate production methods in antiquity that \"In the small-scale processes used by the ancients to produce basic lead carbonate, air and the water used in the washing operations provided enough carbon dioxide to obtain this product\" ", manifestation="explicit", source="caley_richards_1956", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

"caley_richards_1956.T210818" [label=<<b>THESIS</b><br/>Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.<br/>p. 188<br/><i>In the small-scale processes used by the ancients<br/>to produce basic lead carbonate, air and the water<br/>used in the washing operations provided enough<br/>carbon dioxide to obtain this product<br/></i><font point-size="12">"the air itself ... an- cients"</font>>, gephi_label="THES", locus="p. 188", speaker="Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.", text="the air itself ··· ··· ····· ···· ·· ··· ······· ·········· ········ ······ ······ ······· ·· ······· ····· ···· ········· ·· ··· ·····- ····· ········· ···· ·· ··· an- cients", paraphrasis="In the small-scale processes used by the ancients to produce basic lead carbonate, air and the water used in the washing operations provided enough carbon dioxide to obtain this product ", manifestation="explicit", source="caley_richards_1956", fillcolor="#f0faf0", color="#82b366", style="rounded,filled", shape="box", margin="0.30,0.1"];

