"caley_richards_1956.S211600" [label=<<b>SUPPORT</b><br/>Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.<br/>p. 188<br/><i>form: experiment</i><br/><font point-size="12">"This was verified ... this way"</font>>, gephi_label="SUPP", text="This was verified by performing in miniature ··· ······· ···· ········· by Theophrastus. Lead blocks were ········· ···· ····· · five per cent ······ acid solution ·· ·· open vessel, ··· the white crusts that ···· ······ ·· the blocks by corrosion ···· ······· ··· ·· ········· ·· ····· ten ... ········ almost immediately, ··· ····· the solution had ····· ··· · few hours it absorbed enough carbon dioxide from the air ·· ····· ··· ···- ·········· ·· · ············ ······ of carbonate. The statements of Theophrastus suggest that, in the process ·· ·········, white lead formed in just this way", locus="p. 188", speaker="Caley-Earle-R., Richards-John-F.", form="experiment", paraphrasis="\"{Our miniature replication of Theophrastus' process}\" JUSTIFIES) \"In the small-scale processes used by the ancients to produce basic lead carbonate, air and the water used in the washing operations provided enough carbon dioxide to obtain this product\" ", manifestation="explicit", fillcolor="#dae8fc", color="#7c9ac7", style="filled", shape="ellipse", margin="0.05,0.02", source="caley_richards_1956"];

